106.3	Peat	Peat	Peat is an accumulation of partially decayed vegetation matter or histosol. Peat forms in wetland bogs, moors, muskegs, pocosins, mires, and peat swamp forests. Peat is harvested as an important source of fuel in certain parts of the world. By volume, there are about 4 trillion m³ of peat in the world covering a total of around 2% of global land area (about 3 million km²), containing about 8 billion terajoules of energy.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/07/Peat_gatherers.JPG/220px-Peat_gatherers.JPG
